;(First interaction)
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 502013101: Config/Level/NPCDialogue/P10202/F10202001_G43/Act/Act_502013101.json-->
::'''Ruoyue:''' Ah, an esteemed customer visiting Xianzhou from afar. Are you here for a divination today?
::'''Ruoyue:''' Since it's your first time here, allow me to introduce myself. I am the genius diviner, formerly of the Divination Commission, now a humble shopkeeper of the Looking Bronze. My name is Ruoyue.
::'''Ruoyue:''' Whether you're seeking fortune or safety, or simply wish to check your horoscope, to find love, or even to request a name for a child, I am humbly at your service.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I wish to name myself.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option1_1-->
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Oh, seeking a name for yourself? That is a rare request indeed.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Looking at you, and with a pinch of my fingers, and I've got the perfect name for you.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' How about "Noob"?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} That's worse than (Trailblazer).
::::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option1_1_1-->
::::'''Ruoyue:''' That sounds just fine. Your name is fine as it is. I see no need to change it.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} That IS my name.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option1_1_2-->
::::'''Ruoyue:''' I wouldn't have known that one with such elegant flair as yours would have such a resounding name.
::::'''Ruoyue:''' You may not be aware, but a name is the shortest form of a spell. If you're ever in peril, just yell out your name "Noob," and it will surely be useful to you.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You don't think your naming lacks a little sophistication?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option1_1_3-->
::::'''Ruoyue:''' Noob Noob, never want for gulp or slurp. Noob Noob, Luofu's friend, always a perk.
::::'''Ruoyue:''' If you don't like that, how about a fee to unlock "Sophisticated Names" and "Seriously Sophisticated Names"... I have services for all needs.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I wish to know my fortune.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option1_2-->
:::'''Ruoyue:''' You've come to the right person. This is our shop special, the "Fortune for Today." The first try's free. Let me see...
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Oh dear, this scene paints the destruction of the Xianzhou Cangcheng: "Fighting fire with woods will only fuel the flames." Your recent affairs haven't been going your way, so instead of remedying them, you should leave them be.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' We provide fortune-changing services, like the "Evil Begone" bundle for 199, "See No Evil" bundle for 299, and the "Only Good Things From Here On Out" bundle for 599. All great value! What do you think?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} It feels like you didn't really think those bundles' names through.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option1_2_1-->
::::'''Ruoyue:''' Those names are of no importance. The prices speak for themselves!
::::'''Ruoyue:''' Names are just superficial packaging. They can change anytime.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Did you make me pick a dire fortune on purpose?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option1_2_2-->
::::'''Ruoyue:''' Oh, you hurt me with your words. If you don't believe me, let's try another one. Look, it's still the same: "Like birds into nets, when will reunion be, one frets".
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I can change my luck just like that?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option1_2_3-->
::::'''Ruoyue:''' Your luck isn't something set in stone. If everything was already pre-determined, where would one's freedom be?
::<!--Custom String Trigger: 502013101_Option1_End-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option1_End-->
::'''Ruoyue:''' You are our lucky 100th customer for the day, so I'll give you an "Evil Begone" bundle as a favor. This is your "lucky trinket" for today. Don't lose it now.
::'''Ruoyue:''' Do you have anything else you need help with?
;(Subsequent interactions)
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 502013102: Config/Level/NPCDialogue/P10202/F10202001_G43/Act/Act_502013102.json-->
::'''Ruoyue:''' Oh, you're back again? Hold on, I'm reading a book called "A Prophecy's Self-fulfillment."
::'''Ruoyue:''' Well, that was boring. It's much more interesting to talk to you. Are you here to determine your luck, or just to chat?
::'''Ruoyue:''' Whether you're seeking fortune or safety, or simply wish to check your horoscope, to find love, or even to request a name for a child, I am humbly at your service.
:<!--Ends the current performance-->
:<!--Open NPC Menu-->
;(If {{cx}}<!--SubMission Started: 404025502-->)
:{{DIcon|?}} Have you heard of the jinxed A-Xing?
::<!--Trigger PerformanceD 404025502: Config/Level/Mission/4040255/Act/Act404025502.json-->
::'''Ruoyue:''' A-Xing? Well, I may not remember the name along, but since you mentioned "jinxed," I can hardly forget someone as unlucky as him... I mean, he has never drawn a "Weal" stick, but he just keeps on trying anyway.
::'''Ruoyue:''' It's his bad luck that makes him draw a "Woe" stick every time, not the other way around. Of course, I've recommended him a lot of charms and trinkets to help improve his luck, but his bad luck is a bit too... overwhelming.
::'''Ruoyue:''' To be honest... I've always believed that one's fate is not necessarily predestined. If one can stay optimistic about their future, then they will have a brighter future ahead of them.
::'''Ruoyue:''' If A-Xing could experience something other than "Woe," it might help change his attitude about his fate... Unfortunately, he's never had the chance...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} How about we guarantee him a "Weal"?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414255041-->
::'''Ruoyue:''' Huh? Are you suggesting... that I rig the results so that A-Xing gets a "Weal"? But that's just a fake result. It's not really going to change his bad luck...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You just said that one's fate is not necessarily predestined.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414255043-->
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Well... I guess that's a good point.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} As long as this helps change his attitude about his fate.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414255045-->
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Well... I guess that's a good point.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} He said this would be the last draw of his life...
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414255047-->
:::'''Ruoyue:''' I'm sort of convinced, I guess.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_414255048-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414255048-->
::'''Ruoyue:''' All right, fine! Just don't blame me or yourself if we guarantee him a "Weal" stick but he still has bad luck!
::'''Ruoyue:''' Wait for a while. I'll need to modify the jade abacus for divination.
::{{Black Screen|Ruoyue starts to modify her jade abacus used for divination. It doesn't take her too long to alter the hardware, since she used to be a diviner in the Divination Commission.}}
::'''Ruoyue:''' All right, it's done. Would you like to test it out? Theoretically, this jade abacus should only produce "Weal" results now.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} (Divine your fate)
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414255053-->
::You dive into the depths of your mind and meditate on the question in your mind.
:;(Screen fades to black)
::As the jade abacus starts spinning, some kind of invisible barrier separates you from the outside world. In the midst of the sudden tranquility, a blurred yet unmistakable image gradually becomes clear...
::You are seeing the Xianzhou Luofu, on which the towering Ambrosial Arbor looms over countless Cloud Knights. With the arrival of numerous Outworlders, Starskiff Haven is alive with people from all walks of life.
::'''Ruoyue:''' It's the "Luofu," a very auspicious stick! Awesome, let's try again!
:;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} But I thought you should never perform two divinations in a single day?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414255059-->
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Come on! Why even bother with these rules when we've already cracked the jade abacus?
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_414255060-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414255060-->
::;(Screen fades to black)
:::As the jade abacus starts spinning, some kind of invisible barrier separates you from the outside world. In the midst of the sudden tranquility, a blurred yet unmistakable image gradually becomes clear...
:::You are seeing the Xianzhou Yaoqing, which is advancing at a dazzling speed, carrying the momentum of tempest and thunder. Countless foxians, fully armed, are standing on the deck in a majestic posture.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Awesome, another "Weal" stick! Hah, even though it's been a while since I've tinkered with hardware like this, my skills haven't gone to waste after all...
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Now, please call A-Xing over.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Why do you need me to call him?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414255065-->
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Well... it might seem a bit too deliberate if I just call him out of the blue and say something like, "Hey, my jade abacus is ready. Come over here and draw your lot." It might make it seem like my abacus wasn't ready before.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Just call him over and pretend you know nothing about my jade abacus. We've got to put on a credible show, otherwise we won't be able to help him.
:::<!--Ends the current performance-->
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Talk_404025502-->
