:::'''Ruoyue:''' I have already divined for you today. Please come back tomorrow.
;(If {{Mission|Wood Sprouts Anew, Fate Tilts Askew|showChapter=0}} has been completed, {{cx}}<!--performance 502013201 has been seen-->, and {{Mission|Obsequies Performed, A Long Road Ahead|showChapter=0}} has not been completed)
:{{DIcon|Talk}} The Ambrosial Arbor is growing again...
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 502013201: Config/Level/NPCDialogue/P10202/F10202001_G52/Act502013201.json-->
::'''Ruoyue:''' Tsk, that can't be a good omen.
::'''Ruoyue:''' The Luofu has been ravaged by disaster recently. Everyone thinks that the Cloud Knights are capable of solving every problem under the sun, no matter how great or small.
::'''Ruoyue:''' But the Ambrosial Arbor's growth doesn't fall within the scope of operations for the Cloud Knights...
::'''Ruoyue:''' I'm not sure if the master diviner has foreseen this? I'm thinking, probably not.
::<!--Ends the current performance-->
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Talk_502013201-->
;(If {{Mission|Obsequies Performed, A Long Road Ahead|showChapter=0}} has been completed and {{Mission|Wood Sprouts Anew, Fate Tilts Askew|showChapter=0}} has been completed, {{cx}}<!--performance 502013201 has been seen-->, and {{Mission|Obsequies Performed, A Long Road Ahead|showChapter=0}} has not been completed)
:{{DIcon|Talk}} Have you divined for the Ambrosial Arbor crisis?
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 502013104: Config/Level/NPCDialogue/P10202/NPCAct/Act502013104.json-->
::'''Ruoyue:''' I divined when it sprouted, but I didn't bother to check again later because I didn't think it was necessary. Neither its sprouting or its sudden stop came as a surprise to me.
::'''Ruoyue:''' It's just like... like each sign consists of yin and yang. If the Ambrosial Arbor suddenly sprouts, then it's destined to stop just as suddenly.. This result is bound to happen.
::'''Ruoyue:''' As for the impact, I'm not an official, and I don't think it's my job to worry about it. That's what the master diviner is for, right? For me, I'm more interested in figuring out what I'm going to eat for dinner.
::<!--Ends the current performance-->
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Talk_502013104-->
;(If {{Mission|Obsequies Performed, A Long Road Ahead|showChapter=0}} has been completed and {{Mission|Wood Sprouts Anew, Fate Tilts Askew|showChapter=0}} has been completed, {{cx}}<!--performance 502013201 has been seen-->, and {{Mission|Obsequies Performed, A Long Road Ahead|showChapter=0}} has not been completed)
:{{DIcon}} I'd like to ask you a few things...
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 502013103: Config/Level/NPCDialogue/P10202/F10202001_G43/Act/Act_502013103.json-->
::'''Ruoyue:''' Fire away. But I'll have to start charging if it's to do with your fortune.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: 502013101_OptionLoop-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_OptionLoop-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} You said you were once a Divination Commission diviner?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option2_1_1-->
:::'''Ruoyue:''' So, you have doubts about my professional proficiency. No fear, I worked there for almost two centuries, until I was personally ejected by Master Diviner Fu Xuan.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Master Diviner Fu Xuan foresaw that she would remove me from the Divination Commission, so she did.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' How could someone make a decision based off something that hadn't happened yet? Anyway, I did leave the Commission, but the entire situation was a farce.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Even if the Divination Commission didn't want me, I could still run my little old divination paraphernalia shop here. Outworlders who can't get their fortunes at the Commission could come to me instead.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} I've heard that your divinations aren't accurate?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option2_1_2-->
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Of course they are accurate! Who told you that? Give me their name.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' ...Then again, they aren't totally wrong. Many times, the line between accuracy and inaccuracy is... subjective.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Most people just want to know about their fortunes and have some sort of control over their future. In truth, everyone moves in a general direction in the great stream of destiny, but when it comes to actual good or ill luck...
:::'''Ruoyue:''' That's a hidden current of probability no one can ever fathom. To capture such an intricacy, you'd have to invest massive resources and rely on devices as huge as mountains to calculate that.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' So, one of the rules in the Divination Commission's "Three Don'ts" is "Don't divine personal matters." It's not particularly taboo or anything &mdash; just that there are too many variables and does more harm than good.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' But for me? I've got other ways. I provide clients with the most ambiguous results possible &mdash; it's about the limit of accuracy for my tiny shop anyway.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' For example, I don't even have to pinch my fingers to foretell that you will have a small amount of wealth coming in sometime between this week and this month. Am I right? Of course I am.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} I see a few game tables here as well?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option2_1_3-->
:::'''Ruoyue:''' I do business. Divination makes money, and so do games of cards and tiles. There's no conflict of interest.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' I knew a girl called Qingque during my time at the Divination Commission. You'll run into her if you come here often. She recreated this game called "Celestial Jade" from old books.
:::'''Ruoyue:''' How nice it'd be to play a few rounds with friends. It lifts my spirits just seeing them play, too. If I could earn a living with a games parlor, I wouldn't be doing any divination.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Exit}} I don't have any other questions.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: 502013101_Option2_1_4-->
:::'''Ruoyue:''' Come back again, esteemed customer. If you're down on your luck, I'll be here to help you turn it around.
:::<!--Ends the current performance-->
